CHAIMOWITZ, Appellant, v. CHAIMOWITZ, Respondent. (Superior Court of New York City,

General Term.

May 1, 1893.) Action by Jacob Chaimowitz against Tauba Buna Chaimowitz. An order was entered denying plaintiff’s motion for an inspection of papers.

Argued before SEDGWICK, C. J., and FREEDMAN, J.

Charles H. Smith, for appellant. Abraham H. Sarasohn, for respondent. PER CURIAM.

The discretion of the court below was properly exercised, and the order is affirmed, without costs.
